# ⚠️ IMPORTANT: Add your YouTube API keys below

# YouTube API Keys - Add multiple keys for rotation
# The system will automatically rotate between available keys
# To avoid quota limits, use 3-5 different API keys

# Primary API Key (REQUIRED)
NEXT_PUBLIC_YOUTUBE_API_KEY=your_youtube_api_key_1_here

# Additional API Keys for Rotation (OPTIONAL but RECOMMENDED)
# Uncomment and add your keys below:

# NEXT_PUBLIC_YOUTUBE_API_KEY_2=your_youtube_api_key_2_here
# NEXT_PUBLIC_YOUTUBE_API_KEY_3=your_youtube_api_key_3_here
# NEXT_PUBLIC_YOUTUBE_API_KEY_4=your_youtube_api_key_4_here
# NEXT_PUBLIC_YOUTUBE_API_KEY_5=your_youtube_api_key_5_here

# How to get YouTube API Keys:
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project (or use existing)
# 3. Enable "YouTube Data API v3"
# 4. Go to "Credentials" → "Create Credentials" → "API Key"
# 5. Copy the API key and paste it above
# 6. Repeat for multiple projects to get multiple keys

# Best Practices:
# - Use 3-5 different API keys for optimal rotation
# - Each key has a quota of ~10,000 requests/day
# - The system will automatically rotate and track usage
# - Keys reset daily at midnight
# - Blocked keys (quota exceeded) are automatically skipped

# After adding keys, restart the dev server:
# npm run dev
